SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION—Urging the Federal Government
to support and recognize certain land use planning
principles when conducting projects in this State.
1 WHEREAS, Over 80 percent of the land in the State of Nevada is
2 owned by the Federal Government; and
3 WHEREAS, The public lands in the State of Nevada are managed
4 by a variety of federal agencies, including, the United States Bureau
5 of Land Management, the United States Forest Service, the United
6 States National Park Service, the United States Bureau of
7 Reclamation, the United States Fish and Wildlife Service and the
8 United States Department of Defense, including the United States
9 Army Corps of Engineers; and
10 WHEREAS, The high percentage of federally-owned lands in the
11 State of Nevada requires coordination between these federal
12 agencies, the State of Nevada, tribal governments and local
13 governments and communities when engaging in land use planning
14 in this State; and
15 WHEREAS, The Legislature has emphasized the importance in
16 land use planning of local leadership and knowledge along with
17 coordination with tribal and local governments; and
-
