– 2 –
1 WHEREAS, The Legislature has declared that the conservation
2 and development of renewable natural resources is best led and
3 directed by persons in local communities and, as such, has
4 authorized the creation of conservation districts, comprised of
5 members of local communities, to oversee certain projects and
6 measures relating to the conservation and development of renewable
7 natural resources within each conservation district; and
8 WHEREAS, The Legislature also passed the State and Local
9 Government Cooperation Act to encourage communication,
10 cooperation and coordinated working relationships between state
11 agencies and local governments; and
12 WHEREAS, The Congress of the United States has also
13 recognized in law the importance of consultation and coordination
14 with local communities by declaring that it is the policy of the
15 United States when conducting the land use planning process for
16 public lands and the resources of such public lands to coordinate
17 with other federal and state planning efforts; and
18 WHEREAS, A variety of federal laws that regulate federal actions
19 on public lands, including, without limitation, the National
20 Environmental Policy Act, the National Forest Management Act and
21 the Federal Land Policy and Management Act require federal
22 agencies to involve state, tribal and local governments and the
23 public in the process of evaluating federal actions on public lands;
24 and
25 WHEREAS, Managing public lands for multiple uses and
26 sustained yield are also important principles of land use planning as
27 these principles will best meet the needs of current and future
28 generations of Americans; and
29 WHEREAS, Federal law requires the Secretary of the Interior to
30 manage public lands under the principles of multiple use and
31 sustained yield and authorizes and directs the Secretary of
32 Agriculture to develop and administer the renewable surface
33 resources of the national forests for multiple use and sustained yield;
34 now, therefore, be it
35 RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF
36 NEVADA, JOINTLY, That the members of the 83rd Session of the
37 Nevada Legislature hereby urge the Federal Government to support
38 and recognize the following land use planning principles when
39 conducting projects in this State:
40 1. Actions on public lands in the State of Nevada should be led
41 and driven by the impacted local communities;
42 2. There must be coordination between federal, state, tribal and
43 local governments, including, without limitation, federal agencies:
44 (a) Providing early notification to the State of Nevada and
45 impacted tribal and local governments in the State;
-
