1 (b) Providing opportunities for meaningful input from the State
2 of Nevada and impacted tribal and local governments in the State;
3 (c) Remaining informed of the land use policies and plans of the
4 State of Nevada and impacted tribal and local governments in the
5 State and soliciting and considering the input of the State and
6 impacted tribal and local governments when interpreting these
7 policies and plans; and
8 (d) To the extent practicable, developing federal policies, plans
9 and actions that are consistent with the land use policies and plans
10 of the State of Nevada and impacted tribal and local governments;
11 and
12 3. Public lands must be managed for multiple uses while also
13 providing for the economic, social and environmental sustainability
14 of public lands; and be it further
15 RESOLVED, That the Secretary of the Senate prepare and
16 transmit a copy of this resolution to the President of the United
17 States, the Vice President of the United States as presiding officer of
18 the United States Senate, the Speaker of the House of
19 Representatives, the United States Secretary of the Interior, the
20 United States Secretary of Agriculture, the Director of the United
21 States Bureau of Land Management, the Chief of the United States
22 Forest Service, the Director of the United States National Park
23 Service, the Commissioner of the United States Bureau of
24 Reclamation, the Director of the United States Fish and Wildlife
25 Service, the Secretary of Defense of the United States Department
26 of Defense, each member of the Nevada Congressional Delegation
27 and the Governor of the State of Nevada; and be it further
28 RESOLVED, That this resolution becomes effective upon
29 passage.
